Roccat has revealed its new Khan Aimo gaming headset, which features 7.1 virtual surround sound and powerful drivers. The headset sports RGB lighting, a fold-up microphone, and a 50mm dynamic speaker in each ear cup – which feature ear pads made of memory foam. It also boasts a built-in 24-bit 96KHz DAC sound card, which Roccat said delivers clean sound with virtually no noise interference. There is currently no pricing or release date information available for the new Roccat headset.  